[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":688},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F":664,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F":673},"\u002Fvscode\u002F20191212\u002F2147775133\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":644,"date":645,"description":646,"extension":647,"lang":648,"meta":649,"navigation":650,"path":651,"readingMinutes":652,"seo":653,"standalone":654,"stem":655,"tags":656,"tldr":660,"updated":661,"url":662,"__hash__":663},"content\u002Fen\u002FVSCode\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers.md","2023 VSCode Extensions I Recommend Installing","3234565104",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":613},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,40,46,49,52,70,73,77,94,99,103,111,114,122,126,141,148,157,161,169,174,178,187,190,194,201,207,211,220,225,229,236,241,244,250,259,263,270,275,279,286,291,295,307,312,316,325,330,334,342,346,354,359,363,370,375,378,385,391,396,399,406,411,414,420,424,431,436,442,446,453,458,463,467,478,483,486,493,498,501,509,513,520,528,540,602,606,609],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"VSCode is one of the most-used editors in the world, and there are a lot of solid extensions out there. The catch is there are ",[21,22,23],"em",{},"so many"," — and people keep asking me which ones I use, so here's the full list.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"icon-theme","Icon theme",[17,30,31,32,39],{},"The icon theme I use is ",[33,34,38],"a",{"href":35,"rel":36},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=PKief.material-icon-theme",[37],"nofollow","Material Icon Theme",".",[17,41,42],{},[43,44],"img",{"alt":38,"src":45},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FWpA3c8U.png",[17,47,48],{},"Why bother with file icons? We're visual creatures — clearer icons let you find files faster.",[17,50,51],{},"If Material Icon Theme isn't your thing, here are alternatives:",[53,54,55,63],"ul",{},[56,57,58],"li",{},[33,59,62],{"href":60,"rel":61},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=vscode-icons-team.vscode-icons",[37],"vscode-icons",[56,64,65],{},[33,66,69],{"href":67,"rel":68},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=miguelsolorio.fluent-icons",[37],"Fluent Icons",[17,71,72],{},"These all look nice to me, so I'm recommending them too.",[12,74,76],{"id":75},"chinese-lorem","Chinese Lorem",[17,78,79,80,84,85,89,90,93],{},"VSCode has a built-in Lorem generator, but sometimes you want Chinese placeholder text instead of English. The ",[33,81,76],{"href":82,"rel":83},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=KevinYang.ctlorem",[37]," extension handles that — just type ",[86,87,88],"code",{},"ctlorem"," instead of ",[86,91,92],{},"lorem"," and press tab.",[17,95,96],{},[43,97],{"alt":76,"src":98},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqmrQv9B.png",[12,100,102],{"id":101},"eslint","ESLint",[17,104,105,106,110],{},"VSCode doesn't do static analysis out of the box (unless you're using TypeScript). The ",[33,107,102],{"href":108,"rel":109},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint",[37]," extension fixes that — it flags bad-style code in real time instead of at runtime.",[17,112,113],{},"I also wrote a setup post for ESLint:",[53,115,116],{},[56,117,118,39],{},[33,119,121],{"href":120},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F09\u002Fvscode-auto-fix-eslint-errors-on-save\u002F","Auto-fixing ESLint errors in VSCode",[12,123,125],{"id":124},"javascript-es6-code-snippets","JavaScript (ES6) code snippets",[17,127,128,132,133,136,137,140],{},[33,129,125],{"href":130,"rel":131},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=xabikos.JavaScriptSnippets",[37]," generates ES6 snippets quickly — e.g. type ",[86,134,135],{},"imp"," and it expands to ",[86,138,139],{},"import fs from 'fs';",". Similar concept to Emmet.",[17,142,143,144,147],{},"Heads up: this extension adds ",[86,145,146],{},";"," (semicolons) by default. The shortcuts are all documented on the extension page so I won't repeat them.",[17,149,150,151,156],{},"If you want StandardJS style, install ",[33,152,155],{"href":153,"rel":154},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=jmsv.JavaScriptSnippetsStandard",[37],"JavaScript (ES6) code snippets in StandardJS style"," instead.",[158,159,160],"h3",{"id":160},"es6-string-html",[17,162,163,164,168],{},"When you write template literals in JavaScript, VSCode just shows them all in the same orange colour. If the template literal contains HTML, it's hard to read. ",[33,165,160],{"href":166,"rel":167},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=Tobermory.es6-string-html",[37]," highlights the HTML inside template literals.",[17,170,171],{},[43,172],{"alt":160,"src":173},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPeGnxfK.png",[12,175,177],{"id":176},"volar","Volar",[17,179,180,181,186],{},"Volar is the ",[33,182,185],{"href":183,"rel":184},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=Vue.volar",[37],"Vue Language Features (Volar)"," extension. If you're on Vue 3, this one's essential.",[17,188,189],{},"It handles syntax highlighting, hover info, autocomplete, etc. — and it's officially recommended by Vue.",[12,191,193],{"id":192},"vue-3-support-all-in-one","Vue 3 Support - All In One",[17,195,196,200],{},[33,197,193],{"href":198,"rel":199},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=Wscats.vue",[37]," helps you generate Vue syntax quickly.",[17,202,203],{},[43,204],{"alt":205,"src":206},"Vue 3 Support","https:\u002F\u002Fuser-images.githubusercontent.com\u002F17243165\u002F100514730-07384500-31b2-11eb-8abf-9d58a20dd0a7.gif",[12,208,210],{"id":209},"tailwind-css","Tailwind CSS",[17,212,213,214,219],{},"If you use Tailwind CSS, this is non-optional. ",[33,215,218],{"href":216,"rel":217},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=bradlc.vscode-tailwindcss",[37],"Tailwind CSS IntelliSense"," is more powerful than you'd expect — class picker, colour previews inline, all of it.",[17,221,222],{},[43,223],{"alt":218,"src":224},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FN0HtkNf.png",[12,226,228],{"id":227},"live-sass-compiler","Live Sass Compiler",[17,230,231,235],{},[33,232,228],{"href":233,"rel":234},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=glenn2223.live-sass",[37]," compiles Sass\u002FSCSS for you. If you don't want to set up a full dev environment just to compile Sass, this is the move.",[17,237,238],{},[43,239],{"alt":228,"src":240},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fritwickdey\u002Fvscode-live-sass-compiler\u002Fmaster\u002Fimages\u002FScreenshot\u002FAnimatedPreview.gif",[17,242,243],{},"The compile button lives in the VSCode status bar — click it to compile Sass\u002FSCSS.",[17,245,246],{},[43,247],{"alt":248,"src":249},"Status bar","https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fritwickdey\u002Fvscode-live-sass-compiler\u002Fmaster\u002Fimages\u002FScreenshot\u002Fstatusbar.jpg",[17,251,252,253,258],{},"Live Sass Compiler pairs nicely with ",[33,254,257],{"href":255,"rel":256},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=ritwickdey.LiveServer",[37],"Live Server",", which spins up a quick local server. If you need a quick mock server, Live Server is great.",[12,260,262],{"id":261},"git-graph","Git Graph",[17,264,265,269],{},[33,266,262],{"href":267,"rel":268},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=mhutchie.git-graph",[37]," is a simple Git visualisation extension — view Git history visually inside VSCode.",[17,271,272],{},[43,273],{"alt":262,"src":274},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fmhutchie\u002Fvscode-git-graph\u002Fmaster\u002Fresources\u002Fdemo.gif",[12,276,278],{"id":277},"git-file-history","Git File History",[17,280,281,285],{},[33,282,278],{"href":283,"rel":284},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=pomber.git-file-history",[37]," is a really cool extension — see the change history of a single file in VSCode, presented dynamically. I use this a lot for reviewing what changed.",[17,287,288],{},[43,289],{"alt":278,"src":290},"https:\u002F\u002Fuser-images.githubusercontent.com\u002F1911623\u002F52807635-d5043480-306a-11e9-9b03-351b7cda4936.gif",[12,292,294],{"id":293},"gitlens","GitLens",[17,296,297,301,302,306],{},[33,298,294],{"href":299,"rel":300},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=eamodio.gitlens",[37]," has a ton of features, but I mostly use it for code history — who changed what, when, and what they changed. Super useful for ",[303,304,305],"del",{},"finding the culprit"," debugging.",[17,308,309],{},[43,310],{"alt":294,"src":311},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FwbvPJ0H.png",[12,313,315],{"id":314},"vscode-theme","VSCode Theme",[17,317,318,319,324],{},"I mostly use the built-in Dark+ theme. If you don't like that, ",[33,320,323],{"href":321,"rel":322},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=akamud.vscode-theme-onedark",[37],"Atom One Dark Theme"," is probably the most popular alternative.",[17,326,327],{},[43,328],{"alt":323,"src":329},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fakamud\u002Fvscode-theme-onedark\u002Fmaster\u002Fscreenshots\u002Fpreview.png",[12,331,333],{"id":332},"auto-rename-tag","Auto Rename Tag",[17,335,336,337,341],{},"As a frontend dev you'll occasionally rename HTML tags. ",[33,338,333],{"href":339,"rel":340},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=formulahendry.auto-rename-tag",[37]," automatically updates the matching closing tag when you rename the opening one. Saves you from forgetting the closing tag.",[12,343,345],{"id":344},"i18n-ally","i18n Ally",[17,347,348,349,353],{},"If your project uses i18n, install ",[33,350,345],{"href":351,"rel":352},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=Lokalise.i18n-ally",[37],". It lets you edit locale files directly in VSCode and quickly find untranslated keys.",[17,355,356],{},[43,357],{"alt":345,"src":358},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Flokalise\u002Fi18n-ally\u002Fblob\u002Fscreenshots\u002Fannotation-animated.gif?raw=true",[12,360,362],{"id":361},"error-lens","Error Lens",[17,364,365,369],{},[33,366,362],{"href":367,"rel":368},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=usernamehw.errorlens",[37]," is brutal in the best way — any error in your code gets displayed inline in giant text.",[17,371,372],{},[43,373],{"alt":362,"src":374},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0yLexUK.png",[12,376,377],{"id":377},"cdnjs",[17,379,380,384],{},[33,381,377],{"href":382,"rel":383},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=JakeWilson.vscode-cdnjs",[37]," is really handy. When I don't want to open a browser just to look up a CDN URL, this fills that gap.",[17,386,387,388,390],{},"Hit F1, type ",[86,389,377],{},", and search.",[17,392,393],{},[43,394],{"alt":377,"src":395},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002FJakobud\u002Fvscode-cdnjs\u002Fmaster\u002Fimages\u002Fsearch-example.gif",[12,397,398],{"id":398},"vscode-imgur",[17,400,401,405],{},[33,402,398],{"href":403,"rel":404},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=MaxfieldWalker.vscode-imgur",[37]," is mostly useful if you write Markdown in VSCode.",[17,407,408],{},[43,409],{"alt":398,"src":410},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FjPm7V6t.gif",[17,412,413],{},"I wrote a setup guide for it:",[17,415,416],{},[33,417,419],{"href":418},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F19\u002Fvscode-paste-image-upload-to-imgur\u002F","Paste images straight to Imgur from VSCode",[12,421,423],{"id":422},"code-spell-checker","Code Spell Checker",[17,425,426,430],{},[33,427,423],{"href":428,"rel":429},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=streetsidesoftware.code-spell-checker",[37]," — if you're an engineer, install it. If you mistype English words like me, this is your friend.",[17,432,433],{},[43,434],{"alt":423,"src":435},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fstreetsidesoftware\u002Fvscode-spell-checker\u002Fmain\u002Fimages\u002Fexample.gif",[17,437,438],{},[43,439],{"alt":440,"src":441},"Code Spell Checker suggestions","https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fstreetsidesoftware\u002Fvscode-spell-checker\u002Fmain\u002Fimages\u002Fsuggestions.gif",[12,443,445],{"id":444},"polacode","Polacode",[17,447,448,452],{},[33,449,445],{"href":450,"rel":451},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=pnp.polacode",[37]," — those slick code screenshots you see people post? This is what makes them.",[17,454,387,455,457],{},[86,456,445],{},", start screenshotting.",[17,459,460],{},[43,461],{"alt":445,"src":462},"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Foctref\u002Fpolacode\u002Fmaster\u002Fdemo\u002Fusage.gif",[12,464,466],{"id":465},"dotenv","DotENV",[17,468,469,473,474,477],{},[33,470,466],{"href":471,"rel":472},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=mikestead.dotenv",[37]," is dead simple — it just adds syntax highlighting for ",[86,475,476],{},".env"," files.",[17,479,480],{},[43,481],{"alt":466,"src":482},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FovqKZJo.png",[12,484,485],{"id":485},"vscode-spotify",[17,487,488,492],{},[33,489,485],{"href":490,"rel":491},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=shyykoserhiy.vscode-spotify",[37]," lets you control Spotify from VSCode (some features need Spotify Premium).",[17,494,495],{},[43,496],{"alt":485,"src":497},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxswEAGX.png",[12,499,500],{"id":500},"markdownlint",[17,502,503,504,508],{},"I write blog posts in Markdown, so I use ",[33,505,500],{"href":506,"rel":507},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=DavidAnson.vscode-markdownlint",[37]," to catch Markdown issues — broken syntax gets a red underline, making problems easy to spot.",[12,510,512],{"id":511},"github-copilot","GitHub Copilot",[17,514,515,519],{},[33,516,512],{"href":517,"rel":518},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=GitHub.copilot",[37]," is paid, but if you're a developer, I genuinely recommend trying it for a month.",[12,521,523,527],{"id":522},"deprecated-bracket-pair-colorizer-2",[524,525,526],"span",{},"Deprecated"," Bracket Pair Colorizer 2",[17,529,530,535,536,539],{},[33,531,534],{"href":532,"rel":533},"https:\u002F\u002Fmarketplace.visualstudio.com\u002Fitems?itemName=CoenraadS.bracket-pair-colorizer-2",[37],"Bracket Pair Colorizer 2"," used to be essential, but VSCode has built this in. Just add this to ",[86,537,538],{},"settings.json"," to enable:",[541,542,547],"pre",{"className":543,"code":544,"language":545,"meta":546,"style":546},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \u002F\u002F Bracket Pair Colorizer 2\n  \"editor.bracketPairColorization.enabled\": true,\n  \"editor.guides.bracketPairs\":\"active\",\n}\n","json","",[86,548,549,557,564,581,596],{"__ignoreMap":546},[524,550,553],{"class":551,"line":552},"line",1,[524,554,556],{"class":555},"sMAXC","{\n",[524,558,560],{"class":551,"line":559},2,[524,561,563],{"class":562},"sQrFR","  \u002F\u002F Bracket Pair Colorizer 2\n",[524,565,567,571,574,578],{"class":551,"line":566},3,[524,568,570],{"class":569},"sKpQp","  \"editor.bracketPairColorization.enabled\"",[524,572,573],{"class":555},": ",[524,575,577],{"class":576},"sCcAr","true",[524,579,580],{"class":555},",\n",[524,582,584,587,590,594],{"class":551,"line":583},4,[524,585,586],{"class":569},"  \"editor.guides.bracketPairs\"",[524,588,589],{"class":555},":",[524,591,593],{"class":592},"sTRMh","\"active\"",[524,595,580],{"class":555},[524,597,599],{"class":551,"line":598},5,[524,600,601],{"class":555},"}\n",[12,603,605],{"id":604},"image-credits","Image credits",[17,607,608],{},"Most images come from the extensions' own marketplace pages — the original authors' previews are already great.",[610,611,612],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":546,"searchDepth":559,"depth":559,"links":614},[615,616,617,618,619,622,623,624,625,626,627,628,629,630,631,632,633,634,635,636,637,638,639,640,641,643],{"id":14,"depth":559,"text":15},{"id":27,"depth":559,"text":28},{"id":75,"depth":559,"text":76},{"id":101,"depth":559,"text":102},{"id":124,"depth":559,"text":125,"children":620},[621],{"id":160,"depth":566,"text":160},{"id":176,"depth":559,"text":177},{"id":192,"depth":559,"text":193},{"id":209,"depth":559,"text":210},{"id":227,"depth":559,"text":228},{"id":261,"depth":559,"text":262},{"id":277,"depth":559,"text":278},{"id":293,"depth":559,"text":294},{"id":314,"depth":559,"text":315},{"id":332,"depth":559,"text":333},{"id":344,"depth":559,"text":345},{"id":361,"depth":559,"text":362},{"id":377,"depth":559,"text":377},{"id":398,"depth":559,"text":398},{"id":422,"depth":559,"text":423},{"id":444,"depth":559,"text":445},{"id":465,"depth":559,"text":466},{"id":485,"depth":559,"text":485},{"id":500,"depth":559,"text":500},{"id":511,"depth":559,"text":512},{"id":522,"depth":559,"text":642},"Deprecated Bracket Pair Colorizer 2",{"id":604,"depth":559,"text":605},"VSCode","2019-12-12 14:13:53","VSCode is one of the most-used editors in the world and there are a ton of great extensions out there — but the sheer number can be overwhelming. People keep asking me which ones I use, so here's a list of mine.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers","4",{"title":6,"description":646},false,"en\u002FVSCode\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers",[644,657,658,659],"Extension","Frontend Development","Visual Studio Code",null,"2023-04-16 21:00:00","\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F12\u002Fmust-have-vscode-extensions-for-developers\u002F","_czDTlxDRBTTFRusKOruiMAOMAvKib0Jf-txLAZMCfI",{"newer":665,"older":669},{"url":666,"title":667,"date":668},"\u002Fen\u002Fgulp\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F13\u002Fgulp-series-20-heroku-deploy\u002F","Gulp Series Bonus: Deploying Gulp to Heroku","2019-12-13 21:37:33",{"url":670,"title":671,"date":672},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F12\u002F09\u002Fjavascript-sync-or-async\u002F","Is JavaScript Sync or Async? The Most Misunderstood Thing About the Language","2019-12-09 10:38:53",[674,679,684],{"url":675,"title":676,"date":677,"readingMinutes":678},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F","VSCode 'Can't Find Git, Install It or Use git.path' — How to Fix","2025-04-24 09:52:23","1",{"url":680,"title":681,"date":682,"readingMinutes":683},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2024\u002F09\u002F08\u002Fgithub-copilot-tips-and-tricks-deep-dive\u002F","GitHub Copilot Feels Awkward? You Might Just Not Know These Tricks","2024-09-08 13:06:00","5",{"url":685,"title":686,"date":687,"readingMinutes":678},"\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F26\u002Fvscode-vue-custom-component-syntax-highlight-fix\u002F","Vue Custom Components Lost Their Highlighting in VSCode — Here's the Fix","2023-10-26 11:03:07",1784011716040]